inbodydescription.para: < This was initially a workaround of 5.2.4 phantom PhysX forces on disabled wheels, but now (7/22/2016) there appears to be an issue with suspension
< This will forcibly create and enable a collider if it does not exist, which it won't after DisableWheelCollider.
< We need to instantaneously ignore collisions on this, or it might explode, because wheels. The CollisionManager event is too slow to avoid that.
< cache velocity before setting up the collider, to later reassign it.
< Make sure the gravity of the wheel is initialized.
< pop wheel controller to be a sibling of the part model and zero out any scaling
< set up 'fixed' suspension (if no module is defined to set it up it still needs default values)
< force the wheel to initialize here if it turned out to not be enabled.
< apply stored velocity to the wheel rb again.
